It seems to me that we shouldn't expect a general reversal in economic forecasts (from recession/stagflation to growth) by the time this question resolves. As a result, it seems unlikely that risky/more speculative assets, such as cryptocurrencies, will get much of a boost. Thus, I'm expecting the current downward trend to carry on or, at most, prices to stagnate. Positive inflation/economic data/fed behaviour (US dollars are still the main driver of cryptocurrency prices) could change this, but it seems unlikely within the short timeline for this question.
Holding firm over $20,000 currently. It's interesting that half of wallet owners bought in at 20k level, but no sign of major sell-off, yet.
Macro headwinds but expected to be between 14k to 38k, allowing % for wicks on those days.

Clearly a very volatile figure to forecast though the continued and if anything worsening downturn in Crypto prices makes me think an increase on the current price is very unlikely by August the 20th. With economic conditions set to get worse in the coming months and more big crypto currencies freezing withdrawals and cutting staff, I feel that it's likely we see a further decline into the 2nd lowest bracket. I rand a Monte Carlo simulation on the data which actually predicted the price would be under $14k by the 20th of August 69% of the time. To me this felt too high and while a large drop of this magnitude is definitely possible, I'm going on the safer side with my forecast at the moment on the basis that my basic simulation doesn't take into account investors potentially seeing Bitcoin at <$20k as a more attractive investment that might slow decline vs what we've seen in the last 90 days.

Bitcoin and other crypto were expected to trade independently from stock market but has lately been moving up and down with the market, specially with tech stocks. The market is on a free fall and there are no signs of tampering any time soon. August is not traditionally a strong month for stocks. Too early to tell how the summer is going to go but a slow down is expected and worries of impending recession are increasing. The recent downfall of Terra Luna might keep investors away from crypto for the time being. Will need to look further to see if there are any factors that would attract people to Bitcoin. Not an ideal environment for it in terms of public confidence right now.
